<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-3853] Report offsets for empty groups in ConsumerGroupCommand</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-3853</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We ought to be able to display offsets for groups which either have no active members or which are not using group management. The owner column can be left empty or set to &quot;N/A&quot;. If a group is active, I&apos;m not sure it would make sense to report all offsets, in particular when partitions are unassigned, but if it seems problematic to do so, we could enable the behavior with a flag (e.g. --include-unassigned).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
